  <h3><a href="/opinion/50786-provinces-battle-have-have-not-approach-health#comment-4384" class="active">We care about each other, eh!</a></h3>

  <div class="content">
  
    <p>I'm an older woman (69) in pretty good health who lives in rural Nova Scotia. I can drive my friends and older friens to medical and other appointments. My kids and their kids and grand-kids live in many other provinces.  We want to be sure that our Canadian health care covers our needs but also the  needs of our kids and grand-kids.<br />
Here's hoping Darrell Dexter and other premiers will keep up the fight to ensure that Harper's government doesn't destroy the universality of medicare.</p>
	
      </div>

  
